Title: Q510 (HYBRID TRANSMISSION / TRANSAXLE): REAR TRACTION MOTOR: REMOVAL; 2021 - 2022 MY Prius [07/2020 -        ]

REMOVAL

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during rear traction motor with transaxle assembly removal/installation are shown below.

CAUTION:

  • Orange wire harnesses and connectors indicate high-voltage circuits. To prevent electric shock, always follow the procedure described in the repair manual.

    Click here

  • To prevent electric shock, wear insulated gloves when working on wire harnesses and components of the high voltage system.
  • To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE SERVICE PLUG GRIP

Click here

2. REMOVE REAR NO. 1 FLOOR BOARD

Click here

3. REMOVE REAR DECK FLOOR BOX

Click here

4. REMOVE INVERTER TERMINAL COVER

Click here

5. CHECK TERMINAL VOLTAGE

Click here

6. DISCONNECT REAR TRACTION MOTOR CABLE

Click here

7. TEMPORARILY INSTALL INVERTER TERMINAL COVER

Click here

8. REMOVE REAR SUSPENSION MEMBER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

9. REMOVE MAIN MUFFLER HEAT INSULATOR RH

Click here

10. REMOVE REAR TRACTION MOTOR BREATHER PLUG

(a) Remove the rear traction motor breather plug from the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.

NOTICE:

Do not damage the rear traction motor breather plug.

11. REMOVE REAR TRACTION MOTOR CABLE

Click here

12. DISCONNECT NO. 6 FLOOR WIRE

(a) Disconnect the motor resolver sensor (motor temperature sensor) connector.

(b) Disengage the 2 clamps.

13. REMOVE MOTOR CABLE BRACKET

(a) Remove the bolt and motor cable bracket from the rear suspension member sub-assembly.

14. REMOVE REAR TRACTION MOTOR WITH TRANSAXLE ASSEMBLY

(a) Using a mini crane and 2 belt slings, hold the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly at the position shown in the illustration.

Location to Install Belt Sling

-

-

CAUTION:

  • Do not lift the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly more than necessary.
  • When lifting the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly, make sure it is well balanced.

(b) Remove the 4 bolts, 2 upper differential mount stoppers, 2 lower differential mount stoppers, differential dynamic damper and rear traction motor with transaxle assembly from the rear suspension member sub-assembly.

*1

Upper Differential Mount Stopper

*2

Front Differential Support Assembly

*3

Lower Differential Mount Stopper

*4

Rear Suspension Member Sub-assembly

*5

Differential Dynamic Damper

-

-

NOTICE:

  • Be careful not to drop the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.
  • Be careful not to damage the installation surfaces of the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly when removing it.

15. REMOVE FRONT DIFFERENTIAL SUPPORT ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the 2 bolts and front differential support assembly from the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.

16. REMOVE MOTOR CABLE BRACKET

(a) Remove the bolt and motor cable bracket from the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.

17. REMOVE WIRE HARNESS CLAMP BRACKET

(a) Remove the bolt and wire harness clamp bracket from the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.
